# Group PostTags
A tag on a post.

A PostTag resource has the following attributes:

- **Id**: (int, required)
- **Name**: (string, required) The name / text of the tag

The *Id* attribute is managed by the TT api.

## -> /posts/tags/name/{name} [/posts/tags/name/{name}]

+ Parameters
    + name (required, string, `Tag 1`) ... Name of the Tag.

### Get by name [GET]
Get the PostTag with the given name.

Anyone can do this request.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "Id": 7,
          "Name": "Tag 1"
        }


## -> /posts/tags/followed/user/{id} [/posts/tags/followed/user/{id}{?items_per_page,page}]

+ Parameters
    + id (required, number, `1`) ... Id of the user.
    + items_per_page (optional, number, `1`) ... How many groups to return per request.
    + page (optional, number, `1`) ... How many *items_per_page* to skip.

### Get [GET]
Get a list of the post tags followed by the user with the given id.

Any user can do this request. The caller does not have to be signed in.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
            {
              "Id": 7,
              "Name": "Tag 1"
            },
            {
              "Id": 13,
              "Name": "Tag 7"
            }
        ]
